
Videomarks = Video bookmarking or Bookmarks for video

Exemplified at the Dabble site, see http://www.dabble.com/

"Here’s an inevitable idea that has finally become a reality: video bookmarking. Om Malik reports that Dabble will allow you to aggregate videos on your own personal page and use a bookmarklet to add any video you see online. It’s essentially a video-based version of del.icio.us. (And if a rating-system is involved, it will probably resemble Digg.) Om writes:

In less than six months, Hodder has put together a nice little service which will allow users to bookmark videos from different video services in one place. I would like to call them videomarks. I have known that Mary has been working on her new start-up for six months, and raised angel funding from the likes of Evan “Odeo�? Williams and Mark Pincus…See a video you like, say on You Tube or vSocial or Veoh, you hit Dabble It, and the video link is added to your video playlist."
(http://mashable.com/2006/02/02/dabble-delicious-for-video/)

